traffic_visible_response: Vocational Skills Education and Training Centers (VSETCs) are facilities that have been established with the aim of providing vocational skills training to improve the employability of their trainees. These centers combine course learning with practical training to enhance the operational skills of individuals, which is considered an important channel for improving their job prospects [[3]]. Additionally, VSETCs represent a conceptual innovation over prior labor reform initiatives, although they have also been associated with controversial practices such as forced labor and coercive social integration [[1]]. Some of these centers, like the No. 4 Vocation Skills Education Training Center, have faced sanctions due to these concerns [[2]]. Overall, VSETCs form part of broader vocational education and training (VET) efforts aimed at equipping learners with essential skills for personal development and better employment opportunities [[5]].
